This has to be the most embarrassing moment of my life…

😮😮😮

“Brooke.” Chase smiles like he’s really proud. “This is good. Really good.” 

“Y-you…you like it?”

He nods. “Clive and River’s chemistry is undeniable. Their story is magnetic, Brooke. Truly captivating.”

Did he just say Clive and River? 

Sweet Lord and the land of Jesus, I know this man did not just say the name of the character I’ve written about him.

Those words were never meant to see the light of day, let alone land on his desktop. 

Inside that fangirl fiction book that no one should have ever seen, I wrote some seriously hot fantasies, described down to the minutest of details. I put my pen to the paper—fingers to the keyboard—in the hope that I’d bleed out any and all feelings for my hot editor from my system. 

I did not write any of those words with the intention of having them read.

Chase is still smiling at me, and my heart is taking it personal. Up-up-up the rate of my ventricles pumping blood throughout my body increases. I grip the armrests of the chair, and white dots start to take over my peripheral vision.

“Accidental Attachment is fantastic, Brooke. Clive and River together are fire. Their passion has an intensity you can feel.”

Okay, yeah, I’m no longer on the brink of passing out. It’s coming; I can feel it.

It makes me think of this blooper reel I saw on YouTube where a man passed out live on air while in the middle of a conversation with a news anchor. His face went from red to white, and his final words were “I’m gone” before he fell like a stack of dominoes to the floor.

“Honestly, their sex is some of the hottest I’ve ever read in my life,” Chase adds, and yeah…

I’m gone.

Not going to lie, today, we are all up in our feels. 

Excited. Thankful. So Freaking Emotional.  

It could be all of Monroe’s pregnancy hormones going to both of our brains causing these intense emotions. LOL. 

Or, you know, it could be that this book took us on a ride that we never expected. 

CLUELESSLY YOURS was just supposed to be a fun romantic comedy about single mom Sammy finding love. 

It IS all of those things, but it’s also SO MUCH MORE. 

This book is a single mom finding herself again. A woman embracing her successes and her failures. Her strengths and her weaknesses. Her beauty and all of her curves and all of her flaws. And damn, she is so incredibly relatable while she does it. 

Sammy is Max. Sammy is Monroe. Sammy is you. 

Sammy is all of us. 

This book is a bit of an angst-fest (which isn’t usually our MO). There’s a love triangle (hot bachelor doctor vs a successful businessman) and dark secrets and unrequited love. 

There are adorable kids with funny one-liners. 

There’s sweet (THE CHICKEN NOODLE SOUP SCENE. SIGH. ❤️) and there’s spice (THE ON-CALL ROOM SCENE, HOLY MOLY! 🔥) and there’s shock (Just you wait...). 

Cluelessly Yours took us on a crazy-pants wild ride. 

But you know what? It also gave us everything we needed, too. 

And now, FINALLY, we can get it into your hands. 

Thank you for being excited with us. 

Thank you for reading. 

XOXO, Max & Monroe
